Thank you for this! Recently a cat that took a liking to me had a litter of kittens in our yard (the little kitties are around 17 days old now ♥︎) and it’s a litter of five- all tabbies except for one black one, which you can see in my profile picture if you look well aha. There’s three girls, named Siyah (I think my friend said it meant black in Turkish so we named the black one that), Aleena (she’s a real sweet kitten. She’s the lightest in the bunch and has white socks!) and the last girl is Mireyah (she has a swirly-ish pattern and a spotty belly.) The boys in the bunch are Zildjian (he probably looks most like his mum, Stella ) and Alonzo (who is the second lightest, and has more of a stripey pattern rather than swirly like Zildjian and Mireyah.). Momma cat actually has an owner, but they don’t take good care of her. She’s had a litter before, and her owners didn’t give her a good place to give birth (or even enough food) and four were originally born, but two died.. then they gave her kittens away at three weeks old. Stella (the cat) is in good care in our mini shelter/ house we made for her (a bit dramatic, yes, but she loves it so it was worth it 😂). She has a safe place to care for the kittens- away from all the other cats on our street, where they can’t harm her nor the kittens. She has food, water, a litter box, a scratching post, and toys to keep her and her kittens entertained whilst they’re in the shelter. I actually spent over six hours looking for her kittens, I couldn’t find them at first! One more thing.. do you guys know if it’s okay to bring her to get desexed, even though she’s not our cat? We don’t want her having kittens over and over again, we know her owners won’t do it and the cats only one year old. We already have 17 cats on our street, we don’t need more whilst there’s so many in shelters being euthanised.
